, from the performances of the Argentinian collective the Rosario Group and the grid drawings of Charles Gaines to the video art of Singaporean artist Charles Lim and the mapping of global logistics infrastructures by contemporary artists like Hito Steyerl and Christoph Büchel. Together, the essays offer an expanded understanding of systems aesthetics in ways that affirm its importance beyond technological applications detached from cultural contexts.Contributors. Cristina Albu, Amanda Boetzkes, Brianne Cohen, Kris Cohen, Jaimey Hamilton Faris, Christine Filippone, Johanna Gosse, Francis Halsall, Judith Rodenbeck, Dawna Schuld, Luke Skrebowski, Timothy Stott, John Tyson  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAesthetics. 0aArt criticism. 0aArtxPhilosophy. 0aArt, Moderny20th centuryxPolitical aspects. 0aArt, Moderny20th centuryxSocial aspects. 0aArt, Moderny20th century. 7aART / History / Contemporary (1945-).2bisacsh  asystems aesthetics.1 aAlbu, Cristina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoetzkes, Amanda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCohen, Brianne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCohen, Kris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFaris, Jaimey Hamilton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFilippone, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGosse, Johanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGosse, Johanna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHalsall, Francis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRodenbeck, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchuld, Dawna, econtributor.